reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 29, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I bought this as a Christmas gift for my 2 year old great grandson. He loves dinosaurs. He also loves that it has flashing lights and makes enough noise to drive mama crazy. Mama and I love that it is fun but also educational. All the coins you use for different activities store inside. It seems very well made and I think it will be very durable. Highly recommend.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good for learning
reviews.reviewText: I got this for my Goddaughter and she loves it. It helps with colors and numbers and keeps her entertained. You just have to feed the dinosaur whatever it asks for. For easy cleanup you can just leave the pieces inside the dinosaur and then when you are ready to play again just dump them out.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 2, 2024
reviews.reviewText: My one year old son loves it! And my four year old had fun playing with it with my one year old! Great for both ages! It includes activities that both can learn something from! My son liked to try to put other things in its mouth too. So, be aware of that if you can see your child doing that. But the design is straightforward enough that things don’t get stuck very easily. Just have the coins around it so they’ll be more inclined to put those things in instead.
